===Etymology===
From the Middle English word ''blod'', from Old English [[blod#Old English|blōd]], from Old High German ''bluot'', from Proto-Germanic ''blodam'', from the late Proto-Indo-European root ''bhloto'' (''to gush, to spurt''), from ''bhel-'' (''to thrive, to bloom'').

